alan (0.3.0-1) emily; urgency=low

  * Use t9n.library instead of alan.translations (which is basically the same thing)
  * Handle separately the 'Module not found' and 'An error occoured when running the module' errors
  * debian/: control: depend on python-t9n
  * Do not rely on menu.printm() anymore: alan-show-extension will handle printing
  * As menu.printm() is dropped, a new property is added: menu.final_menu
  
  * The user can now add an extension as many times he/she wants
  * [ext:<name>] will now not declare the extension name, but only the menu id
  * To specify which extension should be used, a new option in the configuration
    file was added: ext. (e.g.: ext = xdgmenu)
  * Some more comments in the configuration file ;)
  * Dropped the "main_<name>" syntax: to convert a normal category into a 'main' one,
    just put @ before the category name (only on [Alan] section)

  * Support for headers in __itemlist__
  * tree.cfg renamed to tree.conf
  * shipping tree.conf in /etc/alan instead of /usr/share/alan
  * do not copy the configuration in ~/.config/alan anymore: prefer the config in /etc

 -- Eugenio (g7) <morarossa@gmail.com>  Thu, 11 Aug 2011 23:57:04 +0200

